events.name: Tulsa Golden Hurricane at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Kenny Willekes recovered two fumbles, including one in the end zone for a touchdown, and No. 18 Michigan State manhandled Tulsa 28-7 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 18 Michigan State shuts down Tulsa in 28-7 win

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: Jonathan Taylor rushed for 135 yards and scored a career-best four touchdowns, helping No. 19 Wisconsin open the season with a 49-0 rout of South Florida on Friday night.

events.name: Rice Owls at Army Black Knights

headlines.description: Kelvin Hopkins Jr. hit Kell Walker with a 17-yard touchdown pass late in the fourth quarter, and Army held off Rice 14-7 on Friday night at Michie Stadium.

headlines.description: Freshman kicker Brandon Talton, who was told Friday morning he was the starter, capped Nevada's comeback against Purdue with a 56-yard field goal as time expired and after the win was awarded a formal scholarship.

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Chuba Hubbard rushed for 221 yards and three touchdowns, and redshirt freshman Spencer Sanders threw for 203 yards and three more scores to lead Oklahoma State to a 52-36 victory over Oregon State on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oklahoma State opens with 52-36 victory over Oregon State
